<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98160257727138></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98160257727138><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=3831&mid=98160257727138>25%</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=3831&mid=98160257727138#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Feb 8th 3:26 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Most people don't test the weight reduction correctly. You have to use very heavy items because the weight that is displayed in your character stat screen is rounded. Here's a hypothetical example:<br><br>Your total weight is displayed as 90. Your _actual_ weight is 89.7 but it has been rounded up for the display.<br><br>You move your 6.0 weight item from a regular container to the herbalist pack. Your weight now displays as 88 and you conclude that the weight reduction is 35%. In fact, your actual weight has been reduced to 88.2, and the displayed value has been rounded down.<br><br>I suggest when testing packs you _fill_ it with at least 20.0 weight in items. This test will be accurate to 5%.<br><br><br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
